South Africa Bonds Erase Gains After Marcus Says Inflation to Breach Range

-- B y   R o b   B r a n d
-- 
2011-05-12T13:17:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/south-africa-bonds-erase-gains-after-marcus-says-inflation-to-breach-range.html
South African  government bonds  due in
2015 erased earlier gains after central bank Governor Gill
Marcus said the bank raised price-growth expectations and
expects inflation to breach the target range this year.  The 13.5 percent security retreated 10 cents to 121.20 rand
at 3:13 p.m. in Johannesburg, lowering the yield two basis
points, or 0.02 percentage point, to 7.64 percent. The bond
traded at 121.34 rand before the comments, made in a press
conference in  Pretoria .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  